<br>
A 7th isle &quot;hook&quot; (also known as a &quot;bridge&quot;, my preferred term) is a necro and cleric that have gotten to 7th isle the hard way (fighting up, probably with a guild raid since getting there is a heavy time commitment virtually no pickup raids will go for).<br>
<br>
You can't bind on plane of air so-<br>
<br>
The necro fights a mob solo on 7th isle, lasting about 5 seconds, and dies, leaving a corpse on 7th isle and repopping at his bind point.<br>
<br>
The raid that is going to use the bridge gets ported to plane of air to plane of air, including a cleric.  Once all the raid is on the first isle, the necro forms a group to start the bridge.  The cleric already on the 7th isle rezzes the necro in, so now you have a group with one person (necro) on 7th isle and everybody else on first isle.  <br>
<br>
The necro then makes someone on first isle the group leader.  Somebody ELSE (not the group leader) attacks the keymaster, again lasting about 5 seconds.  That person then gets rezzed (I'm a little fuzzy on whether it's an exp rez or not) to first isle. <br>
<br>
The necro targets the person, who is still grouped so he can just click on the name, and summons the corpse on first island to his location on seventh island.  The cleric on seventh island rezzes the person in (I'm SURE that's an exp rez).  Voila, the person is now on 7th isle.<br>
<br>
The person now on 7th isle degroups, the group leader on first isle invites another in and the process continues.<br>
<br>
With a smooth operation you can get a couple dozen people up in about 10 minutes.  Even with a couple dozen people, seventh isle can be hazardous, so typically the cleric on 7th camps out and comes back with another character and is now a &quot;safety&quot; cleric if there's a wipeout.<br>
<br>
It's possible to have a very, very mage-heavy raid that way since we're the only ones who want the darned crowns.  You really only need a puller (doesn't have to be a tank) and a rezzer for wipeouts-the pets can do the rest with good pulling and some luck.  Cazic Thule mags did it first, and in style, followed by Bristlebane mages.  Both raids netted crowns for ALL mages attending, and it seems like a couple of other servers are going to follow. <br>
<br>
To keep a bridge in place, the cleric and necro must REMAIN camped on 7th isle.  Once you jump off the isle without a corpse and rezzer on 7th or a bridge-you've jumped.  For that commitment of a high-level toon, they may charge-heavy-to use the bridge and refuse to bring up a second bridge (another necro and cleric), but that's not univeral.  Anybody willing to get there the hard way deserves something, in my opinion. <br>
<br>
Correct me if I'm wrong anybody (Gojirax?), but that's the essence.<br>
